.\kafka-topics.bat --create --topic MyFirstTopic --bootstrap-server localhost:9092 --partitions 1 --replication-factor 1


.\kafka-topics.bat --create --topic appointment-confirmed --bootstrap-server localhost:9092 --partitions 1 --replication-factor 1


http://localhost:9092



Find:

listeners=PLAINTEXT://:9092
advertised.listeners=PLAINTEXT://localhost:9092


Change to:

listeners=PLAINTEXT://:9092
advertised.listeners=PLAINTEXT://host.docker.internal:9092



Update your environment variable in IntelliJ Docker run config:

Change:

SPRING_KAFKA_BOOTSTRAP_SERVERS=kafka:9092


TO:

SPRING_KAFKA_BOOTSTRAP_SERVERS=host.docker.internal:9092


This resolves 99% of Windows + Docker issues.